In a message dated 4/21/2002 10:39:00 AM Pacific Daylight Time, 
Motorhead409(-at-)aol.com writes:
> On replacing the front trans mount, is it necessary to pull the trans back 
> or out, or is there a "quick & easy" procedure? 

Hi David,
Other than cutting out the body in front of the tranny and rewelding all of 
it back after installing the new mount?  No.  Remove rear apron, engine and 
unbolt the tranny.  If you have not replaced your rear shift linkage 
bushings, now is a good time to do so!
Eric&Barb

